doc.previous: President Bharrat Jagdeo had made debt relief a foremost priority of his administration He was quite successful getting US 800 million of debt written off by the International Monetary Fund IMF the World Bank and the Inter American Development Bank IDB in addition to millions more from other industrial nations Jagdeo was lauded by IDB President Moreno for his strong leadership and negotiating skills in pursuing debt relief for Guyana and several other regional countries
